li.al:
the term
“information” shall mean any data, documents, reports or
other communications;

the term
“customs offense” shall mean any violation or attempted
violation of customs law;

the term
“person” shall mean any natural or legal
person;

the term “personal
data” shall mean all information relating to an identified or
identifiable individual;

the term
“Requesting Administration” shall mean the Customs
Administration that requests assistance;

the term “Requested Administration”
shall mean the Customs Administration from which assistance is
requested;

predefined
sets of information whenever they obtain such information;
or

indications as
exact and comprehensive as possible on the persons who are the target
of the investigations;

a summary of
the relevant facts and of the enquiries already carried out;
and

„persoonsgegevens” alle informatie
betreffende een geïdentificeerde of identificeerbare natuurlijke
persoon;

„verzoekende
administratie” de douaneadministratie die om bijstand
verzoekt;

„aangezochte
administratie” de douaneadministratie die om bijstand wordt
verzocht;

zo
exact en uitgebreid mogelijke aanwijzingen omtrent de personen die het
onderwerp van het onderzoek vormen;
